This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it focuses on the introduction of QUIC, a new transport protocol for the Internet. It also involves monitoring the entire IPv4 address space and DNS namespace to detect QUIC-capable infrastructures, which is a network-related task. 

The paper also discusses the reliability and security aspects of QUIC, which could fall under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). 

As the paper analyzes Internet traffic, it could also belong to the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). 

Finally, the paper involves analyzing traffic traces, which could fall under the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM) as multimedia applications often require low-latency and reliable transport protocols.
